%description:
Regression test for RFC 3443 MPLS TTL processing (uniform model, the default) in
examples/mpls/ldp (network LDPTEST).

host1 sends to host2 with a small IP TTL. At the ingress LSR (LSR1) that TTL is
copied into the pushed label's TTL (uniform model). LSR2 is a genuine transit LSR
on the host1->host2 path (LSR1 -> LSR2 -> LSR3), so the label TTL is decremented
there and reaches zero: LSR2 must NOT forward the packet -- it pops the whole
label stack, writes the expired TTL back into the IP header, and hands the
datagram to L3, where Ipv4::fragmentAndSend's own hop-count check fires an ICMP
Time Exceeded back towards host1.

mpls_ttl.test (this file, uniform model) and mpls_ttl_pipe.test (pipe model) run
the identical scenario except for **.LSR*.mpls.ttlModel; see mpls_ttl_pipe.test
for the negative case (no expiry, because the pipe model does not derive the
label TTL from the IP TTL).

Before RFC 3443 TTL processing was implemented, Mpls::doStackOps never touched
the MplsHeader's ttl field at all (it stayed at its zero default), so the
"MPLS label TTL expired" line asserted below did not exist anywhere in the
source and this test failed deterministically (checked directly against the
parent commit's Mpls.cc, which has no ttl/computePushTtl/handleTtlExpiry logic).

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.ldp.LDPTEST
sim-time-limit = 2s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
**.cmdenv-log-level = "info"

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host2"
**.host1.app[0].timeToLive = 1

**.host3.numApps = 1
**.host3.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host3.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host3.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host3.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host3.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host3.app[0].destAddresses = "host4"

**.host{2..4}.numApps = 1
**.host{2..4}.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host{2..4}.app[0].localPort = 100

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host4.rt"

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR5.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

**.LSR*.holdTime = 6s
**.LSR*.helloInterval = 2s

**.scenarioManager.script = xml("<scenario/>")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the data plane is label-switched, as usual
%contains: stdout
doStackOps: {PUSH
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the label TTL (copied from the small IP TTL at the ingress) is decremented to
%# zero at the transit LSR, which pops the entire stack instead of forwarding
%contains: stdout
MPLS label TTL expired, discarding the label stack and handing the datagram up to L3 for ICMP Time Exceeded processing
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Ipv4's own hop-count check (reused, not new ICMP plumbing in Mpls) fires the
%# ICMP Time Exceeded that travels back towards host1
%contains: stdout
sending ICMP_TIME_EXCEEDED
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
